好.notes: It is good (好) for a woman (女) and her child (子) to be together.

女.notes: Pictograph of a woman. Depicts a stick-figure with breasts sitting or squatting down.

子.notes: Pictograph of a small child with its two arms outstretched.

components.notes: The purpose of this component is unclear.
龰 is a component form of 止.

止.notes: Pictograph of a foot. The meaning of this character has shifted over time and now means "stop".

的.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 白 represents the meaning and 勺 represents the sound. The character is based on the original meaning "bright white", which is unrelated to the modern meaning.

components.notes: The pronunciation of 的 was similar to 勺 in old Chinese, but they no longer sound similar in modern Mandarin due to historical phonetic changes.

白.notes: Origin unclear. Used in ancient texts to mean "white" and "hundred" (百).

我.notes: Pictograph of a weapon or farming tool with a forked blade and long handle.

戈.notes: Pictograph of a weapon with a long shaft and horizontal blade.

了.notes: Pictograph of a young child, similar to 子 but without arms. Relation to meaning uncertain. Sometimes explained as a derivation from 子 by cutting off the arms, depicting something being cut short or finished.

不.notes: Pictograph of sepals of a flower. Unrelated to modern meaning.

一.notes: A single horizontal stroke, representing the number one.

二.notes: Two horizontal strokes, representing the number two.

三.notes: Three horizontal strokes, representing the number three.

你.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 亻 represents the meaning and 尔 represents the sound.

components.notes: 亻 is a component form of 人.
The pronunciation of 你 was similar to 尔 in old Chinese, but they no longer sound similar in modern Mandarin due to historical phonetic changes. 你 also serves as a meaning component.

人.notes: Pictograph of the side view of a person.

爾.notes: Origin unclear. Used in ancient texts to mean "you".

百.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 一 represents the meaning and 白 represents the sound.

才.notes: Pictograph of a small plant starting to emerge from the ground. Based on the original meaning "to sprout". The meaning of this character has shifted over time and now means "talent".

土.notes: Pictograph of a lump of clay on a pottery wheel.

士.notes: Pictograph of the head of an axe. Likely used to represent a military officer.

components.notes: The purpose of this component is unclear. The modern form of this component looks like 土, but originally it was written as 士.

言.notes: Pictograph of a tongue sticking out of a mouth. In old scripts written the same as 舌 but with an extra line.

舌.notes: Pictograph of a tongue sticking out of a mouth, with a splatter of spit at the end.

文.notes: Pictograph of a man with writing (possibly a tattoo) on his chest. In later scripts the writing was abbreviated to a dot or omitted altogether.

辵.notes: This character very rarely appears by itself. It is generally used as a component in other characters written as 辶.

components.notes: 彳 is a component form of 行.
龰 is a component form of 止.

這.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 辶 represents the meaning and 言 represents the sound. The character is based on the original meaning "to meet", which is unrelated to the modern meaning.

components.notes: 辶 is a component form of 辵.
The pronunciation of 這 was similar to 言 in old Chinese, but they no longer sound similar in modern Mandarin due to historical phonetic changes.

这.notes: Simplified form of 這. The character is based on the original meaning "to meet", which is unrelated to the modern meaning.

components.notes: 辶 is a component form of 辵.
Simplified from the 言 component in the traditional character 這. Used since 文 has fewer strokes while having a similar meaning and sound as 言.

有.notes: Pictograph of a hand holding meat

components.notes: ⺼ is a component form of 肉. Deceptively similar to the character for moon (月).

又.notes: Pictograph of a hand. The character is based on the original meaning "right hand", which is unrelated to the modern meaning.

肉.notes: Pictograph of a piece of meat.

也.notes: Origin unclear. Variously explained as a pictograph of a snake, a vulva, a funnel, a crying child, or an ideograph depicting a pause in speech.

他.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 亻 represents the meaning and 也 represents the sound.

components.notes: 亻 is a component form of 人.
The pronunciation of 他 was similar to 也 in old Chinese, but they no longer sound similar in modern Mandarin due to historical phonetic changes.

她.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 女 represents the meaning and 也 represents the sound.

components.notes: The pronunciation of 她 was similar to 也 in old Chinese, but they no longer sound similar in modern Mandarin due to historical phonetic changes.

门.notes: Simplified form of 門. Pictograph of a gate.

們.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 亻 represents the meaning and 門 represents the sound.

components.notes: 亻 is a component form of 人.

们.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 亻 represents the meaning and 门 represents the sound.

components.notes: 亻 is a component form of 人.

个.notes: Pictograph of one stalk of bamboo. Same as one half of the character for bamboo (竹).

囗.notes: Pictograph of an enclosure. Component form of 围 (traditional 圍).

韋.notes: Pictograph of two feet walking around city walls. The character is based on the original meaning "to surround", which is unrelated to the modern meaning.

韦.notes: Simplified form of 韋. Pictograph of two feet walking around city walls. The character is based on the original meaning "to surround", which is unrelated to the modern meaning.

围.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 囗 represents the meaning and 韦 represents the sound.

圍.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 囗 represents the meaning and 韋 represents the sound.

古.notes: Origin unclear. Possibly a pictograph of a shield.

固.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 囗 represents the meaning and 古 represents the sound.

個.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 亻 represents the meaning and 固 represents the sound.

components.notes: 亻 is a component form of 人.

來.notes: Pictograph of wheat. The current meaning "come" is a phonetic loan. The original meaning "wheat" is now written as 麥.

来.notes: Simplified form of 來. Pictograph of wheat. The current meaning "come" is a phonetic loan. The original meaning "wheat" is now written as 麥.

麥.notes: The top component 來 is a pictograph of wheat. It is unclear why the foot component (夂) was added to the character for "wheat".

components.notes: Also serves as an iconic component.
夂 is a component form of 止. The purpose of this component is unclear.

麦.notes: Simplified form of 麥. The top component 來 is a pictograph of wheat. It is unclear why the foot component (夂) was added to the character for "wheat".

components.notes: Also serves as an iconic component.
夂 is a component form of 止. The purpose of this component is unclear.

要.notes: Pictograph of two hands grabbing a woman's waist. The current meaning "want" is a phonetic loan. The original meaning "waist" is now written as 腰.

components.notes: Represents two hands grabbing a waist.

腰.notes: Phonosemantic compound. ⺼ represents the meaning and 要 represents the sound.

components.notes: ⺼ is a component form of 肉.

就.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 京 represents the meaning and 尤 represents the sound. Based on the original meaning "achieve". The meaning of this character has shifted over time and now means "high place".

京.notes: Pictograph of a tall building. Similar to 高. Based on the original meaning "high place". The meaning of this character has shifted over time and now means "capital city".

高.notes: Pictograph of a tall building. Similar to 京.

尤.notes: Pictograph of a hand with a wart on it. The current meaning "especially" is a phonetic loan. The original meaning "wart" is now written as 疣.

疣.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 疒 represents the meaning and 尤 represents the sound.

疒.notes: Pictograph of a stretcher for sick people.

到.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 至 represents the meaning and 刂 represents the sound.

components.notes: 刂 is a component form of 刀.

至.notes: Pictograph of an arrow hitting its target.

兒.notes: Pictograph of a child with an opening in the top of its head. Represents the soft spot (fontanel) at the top of young infant heads.

儿.notes: Simplified form of 兒. Pictograph of a child with an opening in the top of its head. Represents the soft spot (fontanel) at the top of young infant heads.

兄.notes: Pictograph of a mouth on top of a person, representing an older brother giving orders.

兌.notes: Pictograph of words coming out of the mouth of a person, representing negotiation of an exchange.

components.notes: Represents words coming out of the mouth.

兑.notes: Simplified form of 兌. Pictograph of words coming out of the mouth of a person, representing negotiation of an exchange.

components.notes: Represents words coming out of the mouth.

八.notes: Pictograph of two lines facing away from each other. The current meaning "eight" is a phonetic loan. The original meaning "separate" is now written as 别.

说.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 讠 represents the meaning and 兑 represents the sound.

components.notes: 讠 is a component form of 言.

說.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 言 represents the meaning and 兌 represents the sound.

力.notes: Pictograph of a plow, representing strength

另.notes: Origin unclear. Possibly derived from the left side of 別, which has a related meaning.

components.notes: The purpose of this component is unclear.
The purpose of this component is unclear.

骨.notes: Pictograph of a bone (冎) with muscle (⺼) attached to it.

components.notes: ⺼ is a component form of 肉.

別.notes: Pictograph depicting cutting meat off of a bone.

components.notes: Here written similar to 另.
刂 is a component form of 刀.

别.notes: Simplified form of 別. Pictograph depicting cutting meat off of a bone.

components.notes: Here written similar to 另.
刂 is a component form of 刀.

枣.notes: Simplified form of 棗. Pictograph of a date tree.

十.notes: A single vertical line, representing one set of ten. Analagous to the archaic characters 廿 (twenty) and 卅 (thirty).

廿.notes: Two vertical lines, representing two sets of ten.

卅.notes: Three vertical lines, representing three sets of ten.

早.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 日 represents the meaning and 棗 represents the sound. The form of the original phonetic component 棗 was abbreviated to look like 十.

草.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 艹 represents the meaning and 早 represents the sound.

components.notes: 艹 is a component form of 艸.

手.notes: Pictograph of a hand with five fingers.

王.notes: Pictograph of an axe head, used as a symbol of the king's military authority.

今.notes: Pictograph of sounds coming out of the mouth. The current meaning "today" is a phonetic loan. The original meaning "moan" is now written as 吟.

吟.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 口 represents the meaning and 今 represents the sound.

金.notes: Phonosemantic compound. 王 represents the meaning and 今 represents the sound. 王 is used here because it originally was a pictograph of an axe head, which is made from metal.

鱼.notes: Simplified form of 魚. Pictograph of a fish.

足.notes: Pictograph of a foot attached to a leg.

components.notes: 龰 is a component form of 止.

能.notes: Pictograph of a bear holding meat in its mouth. Based on the original meaning "bear". The meaning of this character has shifted over time and now means "ability; power".

components.notes: ⺼ is a component form of 肉.

熊.notes: Pictograph of a bear holding meat in its mouth. Based on 能, with four dots added at the bottom to differentiate it, representing four legs.

components.notes: Here used as a pictograph of a bear.
灬 is a component form of 火. Here used to represent four legs.

龰.notes: 龰 is a component form of 止.

夂.notes: 夂 is a component form of 止.

灬.notes: 灬 is a component form of 火.

亻.notes: 亻 is a component form of 人.

彳.notes: 彳 is a component form of 行.

辶.notes: 辶 is a component form of 辵.

⺼.notes: ⺼ is a component form of 肉.

讠.notes: 讠 is a component form of 言.

氵.notes: 氵 is a component form of 水.

扌.notes: 扌 is a component form of 手.

钅.notes: 钅 is a component form of 金.

釒.notes: 釒 is a component form of 金.

忄.notes: 忄 is a component form of 心.

⺮.notes: ⺮ is a component form of 竹.

犭.notes: 犭 is a component form of 犬.

纟.notes: 纟 is a component form of 糸.

糹.notes: 糹 is a component form of 糸.

刂.notes: 刂 is a component form of 刀.

艹.notes: 艹 is a component form of 艸.
